            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-1098] Populating exception message with InetSocketAddress.getHostName() can take a long time</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-1098</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>In the PlainSocketFactory class, when a SocketTimeoutException occurs a call is made to InetSocketAddress.getHostName() when generating the exception message. Unfortunately, this call can take a long time. In my case, the address I am specifying is an IP address, which InetSocketAddress attempts to perform a reverse-lookup on to determine the hostname; however, since  the address does not have a hostname assigned to it, the operation takes a long time to return.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I&amp;#39;m attaching a patch for trunk with my proposed fix. Viewing the source history, it looks like the code used to have the behavior I&amp;#39;m proposing, but it was changed in revision 1070943. Based on the source commits and linked issues, I cannot determine a specific reason for the change. If there is a reason the code needs to be the way it is, then I apologize for inconvenience I have caused.</description>
